==English==
===Noun===
'''slam''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]''; ''plural'' '''slams''')

#(''countable'') An act of slamming.
#(''countable'') The shock and noise produced by slamming.
#(''countable'') (''basketball'') A [[slam dunk]].
#(''countable'') (''bridge'') A bid of six (''[[small slam]]'') or seven (''[[grand slam]]'') in a suit or no trump.
#(''countable'') (''colloquial'') An insult.
#:''I don't mean this as a slam, but you can be really impatient sometimes.''
#(''uncountable'') The refuse of alum works.

===Transitive verb===
'''to slam''' ('''slamming''', '''slammed''', '''slammed''')

#To shut with sudden force so as to produce a shock and noise.
#:''Don't slam the door!''
#To put in or on a particular place with force and loud noise.  (Often followed by a preposition such as ''down'', ''against'' or ''into.)
#:''Don't slam that trunk down on the pavement!''
#To strike forcefully with some implement.
#(''card games'') To defeat by winning all the tricks of a deal or a hand.
#(''colloquial'') To speak badly of.
#:''Don't ever slam me in front of the boss like that again!''
#(''basketball'') To dunk forcefully.

===Intransitive verb===
'''to slam''' ('''slamming''', '''slammed''', '''slammed''')

#(''bridge'') To make a slam bid.